00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:28,242
 Mom, I didn't mean for
it to be such a big deal.

273
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:29,368
 Oh no, I've got it right here.

274
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:30,244
Look.

275
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:32,538
I found it.

276
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:33,998
 Oh wow.

277
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:35,541
She was gorgeous.

278
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,211
 Wasn't she?

279
00:14:38,211 --> 00:14:41,798
 I remember her being all
drawn and sunken, really old.

280
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:42,965
 No, she wasn't old.

281
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,676
She was 55 when she died.

282
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:47,303
She was just sick.

283
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,847
There are all kinds
of things in here,

284
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:54,018
notes and letters, baby
pictures of you and Sean.

285
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:55,353
 Mom.

286
00:14:55,353 --> 00:14:57,021
There's 20 people downstairs.

287
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:57,814
Come on.

288
00:15:08,241 --> 00:15:09,909
 I'm confused.

289
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,912
I've never been confused before.

290
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:16,249
I'm forgetting words that
I've known my whole life.

291
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:17,750
I feel-- I feel--

292
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:22,964
I feel my thoughts just
slipping out of my brain.

293
00:15:22,964 --> 00:15:25,258
Something's wrong.

294
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:28,219
I need-- I need
tests or some kind

295
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:29,929
of brain scan or something.

296
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,473
Something's wrong.

297
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:36,269
 Is there any Alzheimer's
in your family?

298
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,062
 Alzheimer's?

299
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,147
God no.

300
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:40,815
How old do you think I am?

301
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:43,776
 I know, but there's an
early onset Alzheimer's.

302
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:45,486
The fact that it's
not very common

303
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:47,864
and there's no history your
family says that's not what's

304
00:15:47,864 --> 00:15:49,323
going on here,
but I have to ask.

305
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:52,034
 No, my father died
of a heart attack.

306
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,119
My mother had cancer.

307
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:54,495
You know that.

308
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:57,081
Both my parents
were sharp as tacks.

309
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:58,291
As are you.

310
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:00,668
But I'm sure it's just stress.

311
00:16:00,668 --> 00:16:02,545
You're working 60 hours a week.

312
00:16:02,545 --> 00:16:04,380
But if you want me to send
you to neurological testing,

313
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,798
I can do that.

314
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,550
I'll make some calls and
set up an appointment.

315
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:08,551
Now, let's see.

316
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:11,179
What's a good time for you?

317
00:16:11,179 --> 00:16:17,685
 Um, OK, um, all right.

318
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:19,604
I'll just-- I'll call you, then.

319
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:27,778
 Uh, Jack still quality
control at Lockman?

320
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:28,738
 Yeah.

321
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:31,282
 They have good insurance.

322
00:16:31,282 --> 00:16:32,575
 Oh, I'm sorry.

323
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:35,453
 Everybody does
that at some time.

324
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:36,454
 Do they?

325
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:40,833
[music playing]

326
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:27,129
 Mama.

327
00:18:40,578 --> 00:18:43,497
DIANE MCGOWIN: So do I have it?

328
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:46,917
 The spec test says you do.

329
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:49,378
It's not totally
accurate but your scores

330
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:52,506
were in the 95th percentile.

331
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,467
 Really?

332
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:56,635
95?

333
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:58,095
That's the best
grade I ever got.

334
00:18:58,095 --> 00:19:00,931
My mother would be so proud.

335
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:04,310
 Do you really
think that's funny?

336
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:05,728
 Probably not.

337
00:19:05,728 --> 00:19:08,981
It's not even true, I
got 95s in everything.

338
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:11,525
So how long before
I'm a vegetable?

339
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:12,568
 I wouldn't use that word.

340
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:19,116
 How about, um, basket case?

341
00:19:22,036 --> 00:19:24,872
 Do you want to tell me
about how frightened you are?

342
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:28,167
 Do you want to tell me
what's going on in my brain?

343
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:28,959
 Diane, we don't know.

344
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:35,674
With Alzheimer's you
can never be sure.

345
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:37,843
One of the most frustrating
things about this disease

346
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,762
is you will never--

347
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:41,138
you'll never be able
to know what to expect.

348
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:49,063
Depressions,
hallucinations, confusion.

349
00:19:49,063 --> 00:19:54,402
There'll be times when you won't
remember how to dress yourself,

350
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:59,532
how to use a knife and
fork, even who you are.

351
00:19:59,532 --> 00:20:02,034
Right now you feel
really bad because you

352
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,953
are in a downward spiral.

353
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:05,704
But there'll be
times when you'll

354
00:20:05,704 --> 00:20:11,127
feel all right, whole periods
when everything will be normal.

355
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:14,255
I noticed you came by yourself.

356
00:20:14,255 --> 00:20:16,340
Have you told your
family about this?

357
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,800
 No.

358
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,553
 You might think of
telling your husband.

359
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:22,096
 And then again, I might not.

360
00:20:22,096 --> 00:20:22,847
 Why is that?

361
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:26,767
 Can I go home now?

362
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:35,860
 Hey, you're home early.

363
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:40,489
 I went shopping.

364
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,741
 Yeah, what for?

365
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:46,495
 A dress, for the
governor's thing.

366
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,914
 Am I expected to go
to that thing with you?

367
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:50,916
I hate those deals, you know.

368
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,043
 You don't have to.

369
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:56,005
 What are you doing?

370
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:57,256
 Nothing.

371
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:58,215
 You know, I got
league tonight.

372
00:22:09,578 --> 00:22:12,581
 Stampy, get off the bed.

373
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:15,000
You're not going in today?

374
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,168
 Headache.

375
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:16,919
 You want an aspirin?

376
00:22:19,672 --> 00:22:22,132
 You use a knife and fork
to eat with, don't you?

377
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:27,972
Answer me.

378
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:28,806
 Yeah, of course you do.

379
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,019
 I thought so.

380
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,646
 Do you want me to call
the office and tell them

381
00:22:35,646 --> 00:22:37,606
you're not coming on?

382
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:40,192
 No, I'll go in later.

383
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:40,985
 All right.

384
00:22:45,948 --> 00:22:50,202
[music playing]

385
00:22:54,665 --> 00:22:57,126
 I got to run.

386
00:22:57,126 --> 00:22:58,168
I'll see tonight, OK?

387
00:22:58,168 --> 00:22:58,961
 OK.

388
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:13,434
Mom?

389
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:53,349
[phone ringing]

390
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:01,357
 On no!

391
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:16,455
 Mom?

392
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:19,541
You awake?

393
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:20,292
 Yes.

394
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:26,799
 Feeling any better?

395
00:24:29,927 --> 00:24:32,888
 Yes.

396
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:34,723
 Is your headache gone?

397
00:24:34,723 --> 00:24:36,141
 What are you doing here?

398
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:37,685
 Dad told me you've been
in bed a couple of days

399
00:24:37,685 --> 00:24:39,103
with a bad headache.

400
00:24:39,103 --> 00:24:41,271
 Days?

401
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:44,274
 I've been thinking, maybe
it's menopause or something.

402
00:24:44,274 --> 00:24:45,192
 I better call the office.

403
00:24:45,192 --> 00:24:48,529
 Dad did that already.

404
00:24:48,529 --> 00:24:50,322
Did you hear what I
said about menopause?

405
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:52,241
 Yes, I heard.

406
00:24:52,241 --> 00:24:53,492
 What do you think?

407
00:24:53,492 --> 00:24:55,119
You've been forgetting things.

408
00:24:55,119 --> 00:24:58,956
You never used to
get headaches before.

409
00:24:58,956 --> 00:25:01,083
Mom, you should call a doctor.

410
00:25:01,083 --> 00:25:05,462
 OK, I'll go to a doctor.

411
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:06,755
 Promise?

412
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:09,216
 I promise.

413
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:12,010
 Hey, you never showed
me the dress you bought

414
00:25:12,010 --> 00:25:14,221
for the governor's party.

415
00:25:14,221 --> 00:25:17,015
 Oh, it's in the, um,
where I keep my clothes.

416
00:25:21,812 --> 00:25:25,274
 Wow, it's sensational.

417
00:25:25,274 --> 00:25:26,316
 You think?

418
00:25:26,316 --> 00:25:29,737
 Not too much.

419
00:25:29,737 --> 00:25:31,655
 Except for the price.

420
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:33,574
 Well, the office
is paying for it.

421
00:25:33,574 --> 00:25:35,409
 Ah, then it's
definitely not too much.

422
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:47,379
[music playing]

423
00:26:16,366 --> 00:26:18,869
 Hi.

424
00:26:18,869 --> 00:26:22,873
Hi, [inaudible].

