 All the stress working
for those lousy lawyers.

472
00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:50,330
Now she's losing it.

473
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,331
 Somebody doesn't
just lose it overnight.

474
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:52,666
 It's not overnight, dammit.

475
00:29:52,666 --> 00:29:55,210
She's been losing it
for a long time now.

476
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:56,420
 I've got Alzheimer's disease.

477
00:30:15,272 --> 00:30:16,023
JACK: Diane?

478
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,582
Diane?

479
00:30:33,582 --> 00:30:35,917
[dog barking]

480
00:30:41,631 --> 00:30:42,382
 Diane?

481
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:48,597
What you doing, Scampy?

482
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:10,118
Diane?

483
00:31:17,667 --> 00:31:18,877
What are you doing in here?

484
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:22,047
This can be very
dangerous, you know.

485
00:31:22,047 --> 00:31:28,720
 I was just thinking about
when I was a little kid.

486
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:35,102
And we used to go to Grandma's
every Sunday, everybody, aunts,

487
00:31:35,102 --> 00:31:39,523
uncles, cousins,
the whole family.

488
00:31:39,523 --> 00:31:44,820
I loved being part
of a big family.

489
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:48,949
We'd have dinner and
it would get late.

490
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:52,536
And my dad would drive us home.

491
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:56,248
And I'd curl up in the
back seat, close my eyes,

492
00:31:56,248 --> 00:31:57,124
and I'd fall asleep.

493
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:02,337
Then we'd turn into
that long driveway

494
00:32:02,337 --> 00:32:06,758
and I'd wake up and see my
house with the trees all around.

495
00:32:10,345 --> 00:32:12,556
And it felt so safe.

496
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:19,229
 You scared the hell out of me.

497
00:32:19,229 --> 00:32:22,065
 Sorry.

498
00:32:22,065 --> 00:32:27,112
 I don't know about this
Alzheimer's thing, Diane.

499
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:31,283
Well you're-- you're really
the smartest person I know.

500
00:32:31,283 --> 00:32:35,078
I mean, even now, you've
still got a real high IQ.

501
00:32:35,078 --> 00:32:40,083
And you know, nobody
has to know about this.

502
00:32:40,083 --> 00:32:42,085
It's nobody's business.

503
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:43,753
You know, the next
time you're having

504
00:32:43,753 --> 00:32:46,840
a spell or something like that,
you can just stay at home.

505
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:53,388
 I'm going to die in a very
degrading, horrible way.

506
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:55,015
 Oh, who says that?

507
00:32:55,015 --> 00:32:56,975
 I am.

508
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:58,435
I'm going to end
up like an infant.

509
00:32:58,435 --> 00:32:59,811
 Come on.

510
00:32:59,811 --> 00:33:01,521
You're not going to
end up like an infant.

511
00:33:01,521 --> 00:33:04,024
 I am, Jack.

512
00:33:04,024 --> 00:33:05,192
And you need to know that.

513
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:08,570
I need to know
that you know that.

514
00:33:08,570 --> 00:33:10,864
 It's an awful lot to take
in all at once, isn't it?

515
00:33:10,864 --> 00:33:13,950
I mean, I'm sorry if I'm not
acting the way I'm supposed to.

516
00:33:13,950 --> 00:33:15,911
I'm doing the best I can.

517
00:33:15,911 --> 00:33:17,787
You didn't even tell
me in the first place.

518
00:33:17,787 --> 00:33:19,748
 Because you don't hear me.

519
00:33:19,748 --> 00:33:22,375
I don't know how many years
it's been since you've heard me.

520
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:26,171
 You've always got to get
your digs in, don't you.

521
00:33:26,171 --> 00:33:30,467
 OK, I didn't
tell you because I

522
00:33:30,467 --> 00:33:33,845
don't feel I can count on you.

523
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:40,518
You're not there and I'm
scared because a really

524
00:33:40,518 --> 00:33:42,395
big thing is coming
and I'm scared

525
00:33:42,395 --> 00:33:45,482
you're not going to be there.

526
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:46,274
Are you?

527
00:33:50,362 --> 00:33:52,614
 Never really ever needed
anybody but yourself.

528
00:33:56,493 --> 00:33:57,369
 Is that your answer?

529
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:01,373
OK.

530
00:35:24,331 --> 00:35:25,665
It's great.

531
00:35:25,665 --> 00:35:29,336
I got a disease that
sounds like a beer.

532
00:35:29,336 --> 00:35:32,047
 It stinks.

533
00:35:32,047 --> 00:35:34,591
 Let me count the ways.

534
00:35:34,591 --> 00:35:36,301
 What are you going
to do for money?

535
00:35:36,301 --> 00:35:39,596
 Well, you know, I mean we've
got Jack's military pension.

536
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:41,848
And you know, he's
making enough.

537
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:42,974
 Oh, bull.

538
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:45,852
It's always been
