00:54:12,249 --> 00:54:15,210
Wait.

810
00:54:15,210 --> 00:54:16,086
You bastard.

811
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:24,136
I don't know how to get home.

812
00:54:24,136 --> 00:54:27,598
[car honking]

813
00:54:27,598 --> 00:54:32,436
[music playing]

814
00:54:35,105 --> 00:54:38,692
 So I sent out tons of e-mails
to all these neurologists all

815
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:40,486
across the Midwest
trying to convince them

816
00:54:40,486 --> 00:54:42,154
to start support groups, right?

817
00:54:42,154 --> 00:54:44,948
And I got an answer from this
one doctor in Minneapolis.

818
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:47,910
He wants me to come and talk
to some of his patients,

819
00:54:47,910 --> 00:54:49,453
just for a couple of days.

820
00:54:49,453 --> 00:54:52,748
But I don't know, you know,
Jack can't get off work.

821
00:54:52,748 --> 00:54:54,249
And I don't know.

822
00:54:54,249 --> 00:54:56,001
You think I should go alone?

823
00:54:56,001 --> 00:54:57,419
 You'll go.

824
00:54:57,419 --> 00:54:59,004
You'll fret about it.
You'll talk it to death.

825
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:00,339
But you'll go.

826
00:55:00,339 --> 00:55:01,673
What's the worst thing
that could happen?

827
00:55:01,673 --> 00:55:04,092
 Well, I could
lose it completely.

828
00:55:04,092 --> 00:55:05,969
I could make a complete
fool of myself.

829
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:09,348
I could drool and fall on
my face and forget who I am.

830
00:55:09,348 --> 00:55:11,183
 You don't drool.
Even I don't drool.

831
00:55:11,183 --> 00:55:12,100
 How do you know?

832
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:13,769
Who would tell you?

833
00:55:13,769 --> 00:55:14,686
 You would.

834
00:55:14,686 --> 00:55:16,146
 I guess I would.

835
00:55:16,146 --> 00:55:17,064
 Want some coffee?

836
00:55:17,064 --> 00:55:17,940
 Oh yeah.

837
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:19,816
 Two coffees, please.

838
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:20,859
My treat today.

839
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:21,610
 Thank you.

840
00:55:23,862 --> 00:55:26,073
 No, $40 for two coffees?

841
00:55:26,073 --> 00:55:27,115
 Not enough?

842
00:55:27,115 --> 00:55:28,158
- Much too much.
- You do it.

843
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:29,117
The bills all look alike to me.

844
00:55:29,117 --> 00:55:32,496
 OK, I'll do the bills.

845
00:55:32,496 --> 00:55:33,413
You have to do the coins.

846
00:55:33,413 --> 00:55:34,206
I'm no good at coins.

847
00:55:37,376 --> 00:55:39,878
Between the two of us, we
almost make a whole person.

848
00:55:39,878 --> 00:55:40,671
 Thanks.

849
00:55:43,507 --> 00:55:46,134
So this is it.

850
00:55:46,134 --> 00:55:47,678
This is where I gave
my scintillating

851
00:55:47,678 --> 00:55:50,639
lectures to several hundred
of Michigan's finest.

852
00:55:50,639 --> 00:55:53,308
 It's so beautiful.

853
00:55:53,308 --> 00:55:57,479
 I was known for my
one on one counsel.

854
00:55:57,479 --> 00:56:00,941
My students meant
a great deal to me.

855
00:56:00,941 --> 00:56:03,485
Mind you, that was when
I still had a heart.

856
00:56:03,485 --> 00:56:05,988
 No more?

857
00:56:05,988 --> 00:56:08,448
 Like, um, like--

858
00:56:11,118 --> 00:56:14,037
who's that fellow
over the rainbow?

859
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:17,082
 Oh, the Tin Man.

860
00:56:17,082 --> 00:56:20,877
 Absolutely empty in here.

861
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:22,296
 Scarecrow.

862
00:56:22,296 --> 00:56:25,799
Just stuffing,
nothing but stuffing.

863
00:56:25,799 --> 00:56:29,303
Hey, Albert, why don't you
come to Minneapolis with me?

864
00:56:29,303 --> 00:56:30,762
 Are you out of your mind?

865
00:56:30,762 --> 00:56:31,763
 Natch.

866
00:56:31,763 --> 00:56:32,723
I got Alzheimer's, remember?

867
00:56:35,517 --> 00:56:36,852
You could come, though.

868
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:38,895
You wouldn't get lost.

869
00:56:38,895 --> 00:56:41,064
We can stay in the same room.

870
00:56:41,064 --> 00:56:42,232
You should do it.

871
00:56:42,232 --> 00:56:45,485
It's a chance to
make a difference.

872
00:56:45,485 --> 00:56:48,447
Listen, if we can
find the airport,

873
00:56:48,447 --> 00:56:49,740
we can have a swell time.

874
00:56:53,660 --> 00:56:56,038
 We can't go to Minneapolis
that weekend because they got

875
00:56:56,038 --> 00:56:57,539
me on the rotation schedule.

876
00:56:57,539 --> 00:56:58,915
 What, you can't
get two days off?

877
00:56:58,915 --> 00:57:00,375
 No, I tried.

878
00:57:00,375 --> 00:57:02,210
Some of the guys are
still on winter vacation--

879
00:57:02,210 --> 00:57:05,047
 It's OK, I'm
going with Albert.

880
00:57:05,047 --> 00:57:06,840
- That's ridiculous.
- Why?

881
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:08,216
It's just for two days.

882
00:57:08,216 --> 00:57:10,427
I think it'll be really
fun for both of us.

883
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:12,429
He's even worse off
than you are, isn't he?

884
00:57:12,429 --> 00:57:13,347
 Well, how would you know?

885
00:57:13,347 --> 00:57:15,265
You've never even met him.

886
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:19,269
 Because you're the one
that told us all about him.

887
00:57:19,269 --> 00:57:21,021
 Dad, this is a
lot more important

888
00:57:21,021 --> 00:57:22,606
than some guy's vacation.

889
00:57:22,606 --> 00:57:24,066
Get off the schedule and go.

890
00:57:24,066 --> 00:57:25,108
 Stay out of it.

891
00:57:25,108 --> 00:57:26,485
It's got nothing to do with you.

892
00:57:26,485 --> 00:57:28,820
 The doctors arranged
for the whole thing.

893
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:30,322
We're going to be picked
up at the airport.

894
00:57:30,322 --> 00:57:31,657
We'll be driven all over town.

895
00:57:31,657 --> 00:57:33,575
We'll be brought
back to the airport.

896
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:36,620
We'll be supervised the whole
time like good little kids.

897
00:57:36,620 --> 00:57:38,955
 Mom, that's not what he meant.

898
00:57:38,955 --> 00:57:40,707
 Give me a little
credit, will you?

899
00:57:40,707 --> 00:57:44,086
 The answer is no.

900
00:57:44,086 --> 00:57:47,714
 Did anyone hear
me ask a question?

901
00:57:47,714 --> 00:57:48,590
I don't think so.

902
00:58:03,105 --> 00:58:04,106
 Thank you, Mrs. McGowin.

903
00:58:04,106 --> 00:58:05,607
Room 502.

904
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:08,735
 Oh, there isn't
any number on here.

905
00:58:08,735 --> 00:58:11,530
 I know, it's a
safety precaution.

906
00:58:11,530 --> 00:58:14,241
That way if you lose it, no
one knows what room it goes to.

907
00:58:14,241 --> 00:58:15,992
 Not even us.

908
00:58:15,992 --> 00:58:19,454
Would you mind just writing the
number in there for me please?

909
00:58:19,454 --> 00:58:20,664
 And on his too?

910
00:58:28,880 --> 00:58:31,007
 Thank you.

911
00:58:31,007 --> 00:58:32,843
 I thought you said
we'd stay together.

912
00:58:32,843 --> 00:58:34,469
 We are, but I
couldn't tell her that.

913
00:58:39,891 --> 00:58:41,893
What are you doing?

914
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:43,311
 It's going to
be too difficult.

915
00:58:43,311 --> 00:58:44,730
 What do you mean?

916
00:58:44,730 --> 00:58:45,897
What are all these?

917
00:58:45,897 --> 00:58:48,984
 The notes for my
speech tomorrow.

918
00:58:48,984 --> 00:58:50,777
 You're not going to
give a lecture, Albert.

919
00:58:50,777 --> 00:58:52,612
Nobody wants you
to give a speech.

920
00:58:52,612 --> 00:58:53,697
 You have no right to do that.

921
00:58:53,697 --> 00:58:54,781
 I wasn't I going to read them.

922
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:57,033
 Damn right, you weren't.

923
00:58:57,033 --> 00:59:00,954
 Look, all you have to do is
just speak from your heart.

924
00:59:00,954 --> 00:59:02,289
 I have no heart.

925
00:59:02,289 --> 00:59:03,707
I told you, it was
the first thing to go.

926
00:59:03,707 --> 00:59:05,459
 Of course you have a heart.

927
00:59:05,459 --> 00:59:07,210
Think of your students.

928
00:59:07,210 --> 00:59:09,087
Think of those students you took
out of that enormous classroom

929
00:59:09,087 --> 00:59:09,963
and helped.

930
00:59:09,963 --> 00:59:11,923
 Diane, I want silence.

931
00:59:11,923 --> 00:59:13,508
 Yes, professor.

932
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:15,761
 I'm not speaking to your
little gathering tomorrow.

933
00:59:15,761 --> 00:59:16,636
It's just not going to happen.

934
00:59:52,923 --> 00:59:53,715
 Albert?

935
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:07,479
Albert?

936
01:00:27,082 --> 01:00:30,919
Excuse me, sir, have
you seen Doctor Marelli?

937
01:00:30,919 --> 01:00:36,550
He's about six feet tall
and he's wearing pajamas?

938
01:00:36,550 --> 01:00:38,093
 No ma'am, I
haven't seen anyone.

939
01:00:38,093 --> 01:00:40,011
No one's been down here
in quite some time.

940
01:00:40,011 --> 01:00:40,762
 Thank you.

941
01:01:14,629 --> 01:01:18,091
 This is a lovely hotel, but
you have to go so far to pee.

942
01:01:24,764 --> 01:01:27,851
 One of the hardest
things for me right now

943
01:01:27,851 --> 01:01:30,812
is that I can't
communicate with my family

944
01:01:30,812 --> 01:01:32,939
at all, especially my husband.

945
01:01:32,939 --> 01:01:36,568
You know, I try to tell him
what's going on with me and he

946
01:01:36,568 --> 01:01:37,611
just--

947
01:01:37,611 --> 01:01:38,820
it's like he doesn't believe me.

948
01:01:38,820 --> 01:01:40,739
He just-- he doesn't hear me.

949
01:01:40,739 --> 01:01:43,325
 Aren't you worried about what
your husband is going to do,

950
01:01:43,325 --> 01:01:45,577
if he's going to stay with
you and take care of you

951
01:01:45,577 --> 01:01:47,996
when you can't even
pick up a spoon anymore?

952
01:01:47,996 --> 01:01:49,289
I mean, how is he
going to do that when

953
01:01:49,289 --> 01:01:50,916
you can't get through to him?

954
01:01:50,916 --> 01:01:53,126
 We can't be sure
anybody's going to do it.

955
01:01:53,126 --> 01:01:56,755
And my sister has been
taking care of me.

956
01:01:56,755 --> 01:01:59,132
And she's been wonderful.

957
01:01:59,132 --> 01:02:04,095
But the other day she got
irritated and she said,

958
01:02:04,095 --> 01:02:07,015
you told me that before.

959
01:02:07,015 --> 01:02:10,477
And I knew from
that moment on, she

960
01:02:10,477 --> 01:02:12,312
was not going to stick around.

961
01:02:12,312 --> 01:02:13,355
 Why didn't he talk?

962
01:02:17,192 --> 01:02:18,360
 Nobody has to talk.

963
01:02:22,864 --> 01:02:23,698
 I have a heart, Diane.

964
01:02:30,538 --> 01:02:33,458
 I know.

965
01:02:33,458 --> 01:02:39,255
 In the beginning,
I was adrift,

966
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:45,845
in limbo, just nothingness.

967
01:02:45,845 --> 01:02:48,098
And then you.

968
01:02:48,098 --> 01:02:50,976
And then I came alive again.

969
01:02:50,976 --> 01:02:55,480
That's when it all
began, when I met you.

970
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:59,275
 For me, too, that's
when it happened.

971
01:02:59,275 --> 01:03:00,151
 Yes?

972
01:03:00,151 --> 01:03:00,944
 Yes.

973
01:03:03,697 --> 01:03:04,489
 That's it.

974
01:03:07,158 --> 01:03:07,951
That's good.

975
01:03:10,120 --> 01:03:10,870
That's it.

976
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:19,504
 I love what you
said this afternoon.

977
01:03:19,504 --> 01:03:22,215
 What did I say?

978
01:03:22,215 --> 01:03:25,176
 You don't know remember?

979
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:26,302
 Not a word.

980
01:03:26,302 --> 01:03:27,053
Tell me.

981
01:03:31,016 --> 01:03:32,642
 All the right things.

982
01:03:35,437 --> 01:03:36,604
You said all the right things.

983
01:03:40,817 --> 01:03:43,820
You know, we could--

984
01:03:43,820 --> 01:03:45,572
we could work off
into the sunset

985
01:03:45,572 --> 01:03:47,157
but we'd never
find our way back.

986
01:04:01,046 --> 01:04:02,380
Jack?

987
01:04:02,380 --> 01:04:04,674
 What?

988
01:04:04,674 --> 01:04:06,426
Oh hi.

989
01:04:06,426 --> 01:04:07,635
 Hi.

990
01:04:07,635 --> 01:04:09,262
 You're back early.

991
01:04:09,262 --> 01:04:12,057
 No, I'm right on time.

992
01:04:12,057 --> 01:04:13,308
 You didn't call.

993
01:04:13,308 --> 01:04:14,559
 Oh, sorry.

994
01:04:14,559 --> 01:04:16,144
 Yeah, we were
worried about you.

995
01:04:16,144 --> 01:04:17,020
 Oh.

996
01:04:17,020 --> 01:04:18,563
 So how'd it go?

997
01:04:18,563 --> 01:04:22,400
 It was wonderful, a lot
of really interesting people

998
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:23,359
to care about?

999
01:04:23,359 --> 01:04:24,778
 How'd your friend make out?

1000
01:04:24,778 --> 01:04:25,737
 Just fine.

1001
01:04:25,737 --> 01:04:27,781
He was fine.

1002
01:04:27,781 --> 01:04:29,616
 So you're glad you went, huh?

1003
01:04:29,616 --> 01:04:31,701
 Yeah, I'm really glad.

1004
01:04:31,701 --> 01:04:35,872
Yeah, there was-- there was
this interesting discussion.

1005
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:38,666
Everyone's talking about
who was going to take care

1006
01:04:38,666 --> 01:04:41,127
of them, you know, when they--

1007
01:04:41,127 --> 01:04:43,922
later when they
couldn't do it anymore.

1008
01:04:43,922 --> 01:04:46,424
And so I was
thinking, you know, we

1009
01:04:46,424 --> 01:04:48,384
should talk about
that because you know,

1010
01:04:48,384 --> 01:04:51,679
someone's going to
have to brush my hair,

1011
01:04:51,679 --> 01:04:58,603
feed me, brush my teeth,
wipe the drool off my chin.

1012
01:04:58,603 --> 01:05:02,440
So who do you think
is going to do that?

1013
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:04,275
 Well you know,
maybe we can get

1014
01:05:04,275 --> 01:05:07,028
a part time nurse or a
medical student or somebody

1015
01:05:07,028 --> 01:05:08,613
like that, huh?

1016
01:05:08,613 --> 01:05:14,953
 Yeah, well, I was
thinking more you know, a--

1017
01:05:14,953 --> 01:05:16,788
about you.

1018
01:05:16,788 --> 01:05:21,835
I was thinking, are you
going to be there, you know,

1019
01:05:21,835 --> 01:05:26,005
to hold me when I
forget how to breathe?

1020
01:05:26,005 --> 01:05:28,675
 What are you laying all this
on my now for, for God's sake,

1021
01:05:28,675 --> 01:05:30,009
you just came through the door.

1022
01:05:30,009 --> 01:05:31,052
 Well, I'd really like to know.

1023
01:05:31,052 --> 01:05:32,679
I need to know.

1024
01:05:32,679 --> 01:05:34,889
 But you're doing
great, aren't you?

1025
01:05:34,889 --> 01:05:40,019
 Well, things are changing.

1026
01:05:40,019 --> 01:05:44,649
I haven't been honest with you.

1027
01:05:44,649 --> 01:05:48,153
I-- uh, I had to quit my job.
- What?

1028
01:05:48,153 --> 01:05:51,364
 I haven't been going to work.

1029
01:05:51,364 --> 01:05:52,532
 Since when?

1030
01:05:52,532 --> 01:05:54,868
 Since awhile.

1031
01:05:54,868 --> 01:05:55,743
I don't know.

1032
01:05:55,743 --> 01:05:57,328
I wrote it down.

1033
01:05:57,328 --> 01:06:00,165
 Oh, well, why didn't you
tell me, for God's sakes?

1034
01:06:00,165 --> 01:06:03,585
I'm not the enemy, kid.

1035
01:06:03,585 --> 01:06:06,421
 So-- so are you--
are you going to--

1036
01:06:06,421 --> 01:06:07,672
are you going to
take care of me?

1037
01:06:10,967 --> 01:06:13,845
 I'll try, OK?

1038
01:06:13,845 --> 01:06:14,596
I'll try.

1039
01:06:17,724 --> 01:06:20,143
Christ, I put the dog out and
I haven't fed him all day.

1040
01:06:26,774 --> 01:06:31,154
[music playing]

1041
01:06:44,751 --> 01:06:46,669
 Hi, it's so cold.

1042
01:06:46,669 --> 01:06:47,462
What are you doing outside?

1043
01:06:51,174 --> 01:06:55,511
Oh, are you having a bad day?

1044
01:06:55,511 --> 01:06:56,554
I had one yesterday.

1045
01:06:56,554 --> 01:06:59,140
Boy, I got lost and I was home.

1046
01:06:59,140 --> 01:07:00,934
I couldn't find my own room.

1047
01:07:00,934 --> 01:07:04,312
 This going to be one of
your nonstop talking days?

1048
01:07:04,312 --> 01:07:07,106
 No.

1049
01:07:07,106 --> 01:07:08,566
I just want to say one thing.

1050
01:07:08,566 --> 01:07:11,653
I'm really glad we
went to Minneapolis.

1051
01:07:11,653 --> 01:07:15,114
I wanted to thank you
for coming with me.

1052
01:07:15,114 --> 01:07:16,824
You may not remember that
you did, but you did.

1053
01:07:16,824 --> 01:07:17,617
And I'm grateful.

1054
01:07:26,000 --> 01:07:32,548
So, you want to talk
about the university?

1055
01:07:32,548 --> 01:07:35,260
The Civil War?
- No.

1056
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:36,302
No.

1057
01:07:36,302 --> 01:07:37,220
 No?

1058
01:07:37,220 --> 01:07:38,471
 No.

1059
01:07:38,471 --> 01:07:40,932
No.

1060
01:07:40,932 --> 01:07:44,769
 You want to tell me
who was Alban Berg was?

1061
01:07:44,769 --> 01:07:45,687
How about that?

1062
01:07:45,687 --> 01:07:46,437
I remembered the name.

1063
01:07:51,567 --> 01:07:54,612
Well, we could go for a walk.

1064
01:07:54,612 --> 01:07:55,863
I'd love to see some trees.

1065
01:07:55,863 --> 01:07:58,032
You want to go to the arboretum?

1066
01:07:58,032 --> 01:07:59,617
 You won't remember
how to get there.

1067
01:07:59,617 --> 01:08:01,244
 I do, right now I do.

1068
01:08:01,244 --> 01:08:05,081
[music playing]

1069
01:08:18,094 --> 01:08:18,970
 See, I found it.

1070
01:08:31,441 --> 01:08:33,401
Lucky for us they keep
all this alive right

1071
01:08:33,401 --> 01:08:34,736
in the middle of the city.

1072
01:08:34,736 --> 01:08:36,321
 Lucky for us.

1073
01:08:36,321 --> 01:08:38,531
 Did I ever tell you about
my trees around the house

1074
01:08:38,531 --> 01:08:40,158
I grew up in?

1075
01:08:40,158 --> 01:08:41,576
Did I ever tell you about
the attic I used to play in?

1076
01:08:41,576 --> 01:08:42,827
 No, I don't know.
Maybe.

1077
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:44,162
I don't care.
I don't want to hear.

1078
01:08:44,162 --> 01:08:45,580
I don't want to hear.
- Oh but come one.

1079
01:08:45,580 --> 01:08:46,956
It's really important
to talk to each other,

1080
01:08:46,956 --> 01:08:48,708
especially when one
of us is feeling down.

1081
01:08:48,708 --> 01:08:50,126
 Because you always
have to be the boss.

1082
01:08:50,126 --> 01:08:51,878
You're always the
boss, every time.

1083
01:08:51,878 --> 01:08:53,254
- What are you talking about?
- You pick the music in the car.

1084
01:08:53,254 --> 01:08:54,589
You pick everything.
- You never complain.

1085
01:08:54,589 --> 01:08:55,882
 You pick where we go.
You pick the days.

1086
01:08:55,882 --> 01:08:57,467
I don't-- I don't
like Elvis Presley.

1087
01:08:57,467 --> 01:08:58,760
I like, uh--
- Who, Al?

1088
01:08:58,760 --> 01:09:00,094
Who do you like?
Tell me.

1089
01:09:00,094 --> 01:09:01,804
Tell me all the names.

1090
01:09:01,804 --> 01:09:03,514
Tell me all the names of all
the great composers, if you're

1091
01:09:03,514 --> 01:09:04,640
so much better than I am.

1092
01:09:04,640 --> 01:09:05,558
 Shut up.

1093
01:09:05,558 --> 01:09:07,393
Bossy, bossy, bossy.

1094
01:09:07,393 --> 01:09:08,311
Moller.

1095
01:09:08,311 --> 01:09:10,897
I like Moller.

1096
01:09:10,897 --> 01:09:12,273
Diane, come back.

1097
01:10:35,064 --> 01:10:37,442
[bell ringing]

1098
01:10:39,152 --> 01:10:39,944
 Albert?

1099
01:11:20,401 --> 01:11:22,403
Albert.

1100
01:11:22,403 --> 01:11:25,406
Oh, Albert.

1101
01:11:25,406 --> 01:11:27,742
Oh, you're so cold.

1102
01:11:31,370 --> 01:11:33,873
I'm sorry.

1103
01:11:33,873 --> 01:11:34,749
I'm sorry.

1104
01:11:45,301 --> 01:11:52,058
[doorbell rings]

1105
01:11:52,058 --> 01:11:53,768
Hi how's he doing?

1106
01:11:53,768 --> 01:11:56,354
I was hoping maybe I could take
him for a walk or something?

1107
01:11:56,354 --> 01:11:57,980
 He's not doing very well.

1108
01:11:57,980 --> 01:11:59,482
 Really?

1109
01:11:59,482 --> 01:12:00,858
Could I-- could I
come in for a minute?

1110
01:12:00,858 --> 01:12:02,860
We usually manage to
cheer each other up.

1111
01:12:02,860 --> 01:12:07,740
 No, Diane, he's
not at home anymore.

1112
01:12:07,740 --> 01:12:08,950
 Where-- where-- where--

1113
01:12:08,950 --> 01:12:10,409
where is he?

1114
01:12:10,409 --> 01:12:16,123
 Had a severe episode
and we had to put him--

1115
01:12:16,123 --> 01:12:17,750
 In a hospital?

1116
01:12:17,750 --> 01:12:18,501
 A facility.

1117
01:12:21,546 --> 01:12:22,838
 You took him away?

1118
01:12:22,838 --> 01:12:25,049
 It's a very good
care facility.

1119
01:12:25,049 --> 01:12:25,967
 No.

1120
01:12:25,967 --> 01:12:27,468
We don't need that.

1121
01:12:27,468 --> 01:12:30,137
He-- he could-- he could
just come right out of it.

1122
01:12:30,137 --> 01:12:31,305
 No, Diane.

1123
01:12:31,305 --> 01:12:32,723
He's not going to
come out of it.

1124
01:12:32,723 --> 01:12:36,435
He had absolutely
no idea who I was.

1125
01:12:36,435 --> 01:12:38,604
 One day, just one day.

1126
01:12:38,604 --> 01:12:39,647
You know?

1127
01:12:39,647 --> 01:12:42,692
Tomorrow he could be just fine.

1128
01:12:42,692 --> 01:12:46,821
Listen, Miss-- what's your name?

1129
01:12:46,821 --> 01:12:48,155
 Linda.

1130
01:12:48,155 --> 01:12:49,740
 Linda, maybe-- maybe
if you can't take

1131
01:12:49,740 --> 01:12:50,866
care of him anymore
maybe he could

1132
01:12:50,866 --> 01:12:52,618
come live at my house with me.

1133
01:12:52,618 --> 01:12:53,995
He's better with me.

1134
01:12:53,995 --> 01:12:56,163
 No, that's not possible.

1135
01:12:56,163 --> 01:12:57,081
 Why not?

1136
01:12:57,081 --> 01:12:58,332
Don't you love him?

1137
01:12:58,332 --> 01:13:01,002
 Of course I love him.

1138
01:13:01,002 --> 01:13:02,670
You knew this was
going to happen.

1139
01:13:02,670 --> 01:13:03,629
We knew it would happen.

1140
01:13:03,629 --> 01:13:05,798
We just didn't know when.

1141
01:13:05,798 --> 01:13:06,716
I've done the best I could.

1142
01:13:06,716 --> 01:13:07,508
I'm sorry.

1143
01:13:27,153 --> 01:13:29,447
 I'm sorry about your friend.

1144
01:13:29,447 --> 01:13:30,740
 Albert.

1145
01:13:30,740 --> 01:13:32,825
His name is Albert.

1146
01:13:32,825 --> 01:13:34,702
 Albert.

1147
01:13:34,702 --> 01:13:36,037
You'll meet other people.

1148
01:13:36,037 --> 01:13:38,080
It's not the end of the world.

1149
01:13:38,080 --> 01:13:39,165
 It's the end of my world.

1150
01:13:42,251 --> 01:13:45,713
Albert's gone and
I'm right behind him.

1151
01:13:45,713 --> 01:13:51,385
I'm losing a little more
of myself every day.

1152
01:13:51,385 --> 01:13:54,221
Pretty soon I won't even exist.

1153
01:13:54,221 --> 01:13:56,057
 Come on, don't talk like that.

1154
01:13:59,143 --> 01:14:02,146
I'll ask Sean to check in
on you later, all right?

1155
01:14:02,146 --> 01:14:03,939
 No, don't ask him.

1156
01:14:03,939 --> 01:14:05,066
Don't ask him anything.

1157
01:14:19,080 --> 01:14:20,456
 Yeah, I could take care of it.

1158
01:14:20,456 --> 01:14:22,416
Just make sure I get
all the paperwork, OK?

1159
01:14:22,416 --> 01:14:24,251
 Who is that?

1160
01:14:24,251 --> 01:14:25,795
 Uh, I got to go now.

1161
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:27,004
So I'll see you later.

1162
01:14:27,004 --> 01:14:28,422
Bye bye.

1163
01:14:28,422 --> 01:14:29,799
That was the night
shift foreman.

1164
01:14:29,799 --> 01:14:31,759
I had to check in.

1165
01:14:31,759 --> 01:14:33,260
 Liar.

1166
01:14:33,260 --> 01:14:34,595
 I'm not lying.

1167
01:14:34,595 --> 01:14:35,471
 It was Paula, wasn't it?

1168
01:14:35,471 --> 01:14:36,764
 What?

1169
01:14:36,764 --> 01:14:38,474
 I know you've been
talking to Paula.

1170
01:14:38,474 --> 01:14:40,810
 Sure, I told you I was talking
to her about finding someone

1171
01:14:40,810 --> 01:14:43,145
to come in a couple of times a
week and help out around here,

1172
01:14:43,145 --> 01:14:44,480
keep an eye on things.

1173
01:14:44,480 --> 01:14:45,856
 Things, keep an eye on things.

1174
01:14:45,856 --> 01:14:46,732
 Stop it, Diane.

1175
01:14:46,732 --> 01:14:47,775
This ain't funny.

1176
01:14:47,775 --> 01:14:49,193
 I know the plan.

1177
01:14:49,193 --> 01:14:50,236
 What plan?

1178
01:14:50,236 --> 01:14:51,862
- You and Paula.
- Oh boy.

1179
01:14:51,862 --> 01:14:53,781
 You're planning to put me
in a facility, aren't you?

1180
01:14:53,781 --> 01:14:55,324
 I don't know what
you're talking about.

1181
01:14:55,324 --> 01:14:56,534
 A facility.

1182
01:14:56,534 --> 01:14:58,494
A facility.

1183
01:14:58,494 --> 01:15:00,037
Before I get to be
a problem for you.

1184
01:15:00,037 --> 01:15:01,580
 Don't be ridiculous.

1185
01:15:01,580 --> 01:15:03,916
 Because I could tell you
right now, I'm not going.

1186
01:15:03,916 --> 01:15:05,835
And I can tell you that
nobody is going to force

1187
01:15:05,835 --> 01:15:07,253
you to go anywhere, sweetheart.

1188
01:15:07,253 --> 01:15:08,504
But I got to go to work now.

1189
01:15:08,504 --> 01:15:09,672
 Sure you do.

1190
01:15:09,672 --> 01:15:10,715
You're such a liar.

1191
01:15:10,715 --> 01:15:12,007
 Please.
This is getting old.

1192
01:15:12,007 --> 01:15:13,259
 I'm onto you.

1193
01:15:13,259 --> 01:15:14,719
 I can't take the
fighting anymore.

1194
01:15:14,719 --> 01:15:16,095
 You're such a liar.
You're not going to work.

1195
01:15:16,095 --> 01:15:17,638
 Well, this is the truth.

1196
01:15:17,638 --> 01:15:18,556
I'm out of here.

1197
01:15:18,556 --> 01:15:19,348
 Liar!

1198
01:15:25,146 --> 01:15:26,605
I don't know you, lady.

1199
01:15:26,605 --> 01:15:27,982
Get out of my house!

1200
01:16:12,151 --> 01:16:12,902
 Anybody home?

1201
01:16:26,916 --> 01:16:28,501
Yeah, Trace, it's dad.

1202
01:16:28,501 --> 01:16:29,502
I just got in.

1203
01:16:29,502 --> 01:16:31,295
Look, mom's car is not here.

1204
01:16:31,295 --> 01:16:33,172
Is she over there?

1205
01:16:33,172 --> 01:16:35,257
Nah.
Yeah, that's all right.

1206
01:16:35,257 --> 01:16:36,425
Yeah, you're right.

1207
01:16:36,425 --> 01:16:38,093
She probably told
me and I forgot.

1208
01:16:38,093 --> 01:16:39,011
All right, thanks, love.

1209
01:16:39,011 --> 01:16:39,762
Bye bye.

1210
01:17:58,424 --> 01:18:00,384
I called Albert's
house but his sister

1211
01:18:00,384 --> 01:18:03,762
told me they hadn't seen or
heard from her since yesterday.

1212
01:18:03,762 --> 01:18:06,640
Do you know if Diane
had a key to her office?

1213
01:18:06,640 --> 01:18:09,810
Well, I didn't think so.

1214
01:18:09,810 --> 01:18:13,355
No, Jenny didn't know either.

1215
01:18:13,355 --> 01:18:14,440
I called the police.

1216
01:18:14,440 --> 01:18:15,608
They won't touch it.

1217
01:18:15,608 --> 01:18:16,942
It's too early.

1218
01:18:16,942 --> 01:18:19,278
I say it's too soon.

1219
01:18:19,278 --> 01:18:20,613
Yeah.

1220
01:18:20,613 --> 01:18:22,031
No, it's all right.

1221
01:18:22,031 --> 01:18:23,532
Yeah, I will when I hear.

1222
01:18:23,532 --> 01:18:24,325
Thank you, Paula.

1223
01:18:56,482 --> 01:18:57,274
 Mom.

1224
01:19:01,362 --> 01:19:02,738
Must have been so hard for you.

1225
01:19:10,371 --> 01:19:11,246
Why didn't you tell me?

1226
01:20:43,047 --> 01:20:44,465
We didn't have those
roller blade, things.

1227
01:20:44,465 --> 01:20:45,841
We had these.

1228
01:20:45,841 --> 01:20:48,010
I used to ride like the wind.

1229
01:20:48,010 --> 01:20:50,095
There goes Diane,
they used to say.

1230
01:20:50,095 --> 01:20:51,388
She's going to
crack her head open.

1231
01:21:45,442 --> 01:21:47,444
I remember her.

1232
01:21:47,444 --> 01:21:50,072
I remember this girl.

1233
01:21:50,072 --> 01:21:54,118
She was fearless and loud.

1234
01:21:54,118 --> 01:21:56,495
She had a big mouth, even then.

1235
01:21:56,495 --> 01:21:57,371
I led all the sit-ins.

1236
01:22:00,582 --> 01:22:03,001
You hear that, Albert?

1237
01:22:03,001 --> 01:22:04,920
I never was the silent type.

1238
01:23:30,547 --> 01:23:33,550
JACK: Diane?

1239
01:23:33,550 --> 01:23:34,593
Diane, where are you?

1240
01:23:37,471 --> 01:23:38,388
Hey, Scampy.

1241
01:23:38,388 --> 01:23:40,265
How are you doing, kid?

1242
01:23:40,265 --> 01:23:41,058
There you are.

1243
01:23:46,647 --> 01:23:47,522
Well, it's been awhile.

1244
01:23:56,114 --> 01:23:56,949
Come on, I'll help you down.

1245
01:23:59,993 --> 01:24:03,205
- No.
- It's me, Jack.

1246
01:24:03,205 --> 01:24:05,290
Don't be afraid.

1247
01:24:05,290 --> 01:24:08,252
 I'm not afraid.

1248
01:24:08,252 --> 01:24:14,383
I've been here a long
time, maybe a week.

1249
01:24:14,383 --> 01:24:17,386
 No, just overnight

1250
01:24:17,386 --> 01:24:19,596
 Really?

1251
01:24:19,596 --> 01:24:21,640
 Just one night but I missed
you like it was a week.

1252
01:24:26,061 --> 01:24:27,813
Come on.

1253
01:24:27,813 --> 01:24:28,563
Let's go home, kid.

1254
01:24:31,900 --> 01:24:34,278
 You can't just try.

1255
01:24:37,322 --> 01:24:38,115
It's not enough.

1256
01:24:42,953 --> 01:24:45,247
 I know.

1257
01:24:45,247 --> 01:24:46,123
I'm going to take care of you.

1258
01:24:48,792 --> 01:24:50,294
Whatever happens,
I'll be there for you.

1259
01:24:50,294 --> 01:24:51,086
I promise.

1260
01:24:56,091 --> 01:24:56,967
Hey, come on.

1261
01:25:04,391 --> 01:25:08,103
You got to trust me, see.

1262
01:25:08,103 --> 01:25:09,521
Because I heard you.

1263
01:25:09,521 --> 01:25:11,481
And now I know what you
meant about being safe.

1264
01:25:14,651 --> 01:25:15,527
 You did.

1265
01:25:15,527 --> 01:25:16,945
You heard me.

1266
01:25:16,945 --> 01:25:17,738
 Uh huh.

1267
01:25:22,868 --> 01:25:23,660
 Jack.

1268
01:25:26,747 --> 01:25:28,123
I'm not going to lose myself.

1269
01:25:31,418 --> 01:25:35,213
I remembered who I am.

1270
01:25:35,213 --> 01:25:40,093
No, whatever happens
to my mind or my body,

1271
01:25:40,093 --> 01:25:43,638
who I am isn't going to go away.

1272
01:25:43,638 --> 01:25:47,809
I'm not going to disappear.

1273
01:25:47,809 --> 01:25:50,854
Still Diane.

1274
01:25:50,854 --> 01:25:53,106
Diane with
Alzheimer's, but Diane.

1275
01:26:10,540 --> 01:26:15,170
 I'll never forget you and
what you meant in my life.

1276
01:26:18,173 --> 01:26:25,514
And even when you don't
know me, I'll know you.

1277
01:26:25,514 --> 01:26:26,431
I promise.

1278
01:26:26,431 --> 01:26:30,560
[music playing]
